    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-11-16T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-11-16T12:00:00-05:00" n="54"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d54">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">710 Consultation (4)/11–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-11-16T13:00:00-04:00"
                            >November 16, 1944—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:38 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1798. Department’s circular November 14, 7 p.m.<note n="42" xml:id="d54fn42">Not
                        printed. This circular authorized the presentation of the text contained in
                        the circular of November 12, for which see telegram 2006, November 12, 11
                        a.m., to Mexico City, <ref target="#pg_43">p. 43</ref>.</note> Memorandum
                    handed Foreign Minister November 14. He read it aloud and expressed his personal
                    satisfaction without [<hi rend="italic">with our?</hi>] point of view but said
                    he would discuss it with President and Vice President. He emphatically expressed
                    approval of plan that Argentina present its case at conclusion of conference on
                    postwar and peace matters and not at beginning.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
